<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FC87FADCA46E" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="B93AEAA7FFFD5616FF46FC87FE2AA427" box="[199,467,798,823]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93AEAA7FFFD5616FF46FC87FE35A426" bold="true" box="[199,460,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
(1) Tegmina mainly brown on corium and with a C-shaped black marking on nodal line (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FF55FCDBFEB3A44A" box="[212,330,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
); (2) hind wings with apex and sutural margin black-brown (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FB92FCDBFB70A44A" box="[1043,1161,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
); (3) numerous veinlets visible on hind wings, suffused with white or blue-green on disc (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FCF4FCFFFC1DA46E" box="[885,996,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
); (4) all legs red (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FB2BFCFFFAEEA46E" box="[1194,1303,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354653EFFFD5616FF46FC13FCD1A4B2" box="[199,808,906,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FC13FCD1A4B2" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" box="[199,808,906,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="B93AEAA7FFFD5616FF46FC13FE99A4B3" box="[199,352,906,931]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93AEAA7FFFD5616FF46FC13FEA0A4B2" bold="true" box="[199,345,906,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Known from Peleng Island of 
<collectingRegion id="498AF857FFFD5616FD3AFC13FCDDA4B2" box="[699,804,906,931]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354653EFFFD5616FF46FC37FC3BA162" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FC37FCF9A4D6" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" box="[199,768,942,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="B93AEAA7FFFD5616FF46FC37FEA0A4D6" bold="true" box="[199,345,942,967]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
LT: 
<specimenCount id="9D48FD3CFFFD5616FE0DFC36FE5AA4D7" box="[396,419,943,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: (n = 3): 
<quantity id="4CB69B50FFFD5616FD8AFC37FD96A4D7" box="[523,623,942,967]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.03" pageId="5" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="30.3">30.3 mm</quantity>
(30.0–30.5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FC4AFA71A346" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
HEAD. Red; cephalic process reaching or nearly reaching posterior margin of vertex; disc of vertex wrinkled with lateral and posterior margins carinate; frons coriaceous, covered with short golden hairs and with 2 longitudinal obsolete carinae on dorsal half, barely visible (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FCADFB83FC3EA322" box="[812,967,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Figs. 10 C–D</figureCitation>
); labium surpassing hind trochanters (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FAEEFB83FF36A346" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
); pedicel of antennae kidney-shaped with flagellum inserted dorso-laterally; ratio BV/LV: 4.0; BF/LF: 1.05.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FBFAFE1EA3D2" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
THORAX. Pro- and mesonotum red as head; pronotum with 2 impressed points on disc and numerous minute black points; median carina obsolete, barely distinct; mesonotum wrinkled without carina (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FB0BFB1FFADAA38E" box="[1162,1315,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Figs. 10 C, D</figureCitation>
); ratio BT/ LP + LM: 1.23; LM/LP: 1.59.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FB57FCB9A28A" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
Tegmina: brown with base of corium red and curved yellow band at mid-length, not extending beyong costal vein; irregular yellow markings along sutural margin of clavus; nodal line with C-shaped black marking in middle; sometimes greenish markings between yellow band and C-shaped marking, and on clavus; membrane dark brownblack with veins white and green and base whitish; pale whitish spot along sutural margin, after clavus (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FAA1FAA3FA76A242" box="[1312,1423,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
); ventrally coloured like dorsally except band of white waxy at level of dorsal yellow markings, and narrow band of white wax along nodal line (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FE54FA1BFDBBA28A" box="[469,578,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
); ratio LTg/BTg: 2.12.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46FA3FFD20A116" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
Hind wings: base red; disc dark olivaceous green or dark brown; membrane and sutural third dark brownblack; veinlets blue-green on disc and white-green on brown-black parts (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FC5EFA53FBABA2F2" box="[991,1106,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
); ventrally, a narrow band of white wax between disc and membrane (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FDDEFA77FD32A116" box="[607,715,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46F98AFD96A15E" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
Legs: entirely red; anterior femora very slightly inflated apically; hind tibiae with 5 lateral spines, basal one big and sharp, and 7 apical spines (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FE75F9AFFD98A15E" box="[500,609,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136B5FFFD5616FF46F9C3FC3BA162" blockId="5.[151,1436,690,1651]" box="[199,962,1626,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">
Abdomen: yellow-orange with external genitalia red (
<figureCitation id="13752A30FFFD5616FCA0F9C3FC4FA162" box="[801,950,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-49@10.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. 9. Scamandra vanvyvei; 10. S. vanvyvei pelengana. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view. C. vertex, pro and mesonotum, dorsal view; D. frons, normal view; E. habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6507542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6507542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="139">Figs 10 A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
